    <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Then follow each line down</h2>
            <p class="section-subtitle">Tracks = chronology. Surfaces = institutional framing.</p>

            <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-dim); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 24px;">Hover over any date to highlight matching events across all three tracks.</p>

            <div class="tracks-grid">
                <article class="track red" id="track-goldtex" aria-labelledby="track-building">
                    <h3 id="track-building">Track 1 - The Building</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li data-date="2025-09"><time datetime="2025-09">Sept 2025</time>Central HVAC fails. Not repaired.</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-12-08"><time datetime="2025-12-08">Dec 8, 2025</time>The building installs a Hanukkah display in the assault lobby — gold menorah, Star of David, stuffed bears in yarmulkes. 108 days after the antisemitic assault in the same space. Justin sees it as recognition. It keeps him in the building. The transfer request remains denied.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-02-28"><time datetime="2026-02-28">Feb 28, 2026</time>Rental license expires; rent collection continues.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-04-01"><time datetime="2026-04-01">Apr 1, 2026</time>Portable AC installed in Unit 806.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-04-06"><time datetime="2026-04-06">Apr 6, 2026</time>FSK tape applied to exhaust hose; FLIR 102-114 F; documented off-gassing begins.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-04-10"><time datetime="2026-04-10">Apr 10, 2026</time>Dr. Fabi letter documents airborne contaminant exposure.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-04-15"><time datetime="2026-04-15">Apr 15, 2026</time>Leasing-office video: direct notice, no dispute, three harm-continuing options. Police called on Justin. Non-renewal issued.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-04"><time datetime="2026-05-04">May 4, 2026</time>Notice to Quit ("defiant trespasser").</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-13"><time datetime="2026-05-13">May 13, 2026</time>SERVPRO refuses remediation: exceeds residential scope.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-24"><time datetime="2026-05-24">May 24, 2026</time>Second acute exposure. Greystar begins post-fire remediation on Floor 8 — directly below Unit 806 — without notifying the chemically sensitive tenant whose lease is still active. Symptoms within minutes: headache, dizziness, cognitive impairment, fine motor degradation. Third documented exclusion from building-wide safety communication.</li>
                    </ol>
                </article>

                <article class="track teal" id="track-talley" aria-labelledby="track-assault">
                    <h3 id="track-assault">Track 2 - The Assault / System response</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li data-date="2025-07"><time datetime="2025-07">Summer 2025</time>Resident Stephen Talley directs Justin to antisemitic Twitter content — not accidentally shared, directed at him. Justin reports the content to building management on three documented occasions. The connection matters: the man who would assault him weeks later is the man who first weaponized the hate speech. The protected activity (reporting antisemitism) and the attacker are linked in a single causal chain. Three reports. Three times the building does nothing.</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-08-22"><time datetime="2025-08-22">Aug 22, 2025</time>11-minute assault. Orbital fracture, broken nose, broken jaw.</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-08-22"><time datetime="2025-08-22">Aug 22, 2025</time>Front desk tells police Justin was aggressor and no video exists.</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-09-18"><time datetime="2025-09-18">Sept 18, 2025</time>Bercovitch preservation letter sent by certified mail.</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-10-06"><time datetime="2025-10-06">Oct 6, 2025</time>Kane warning letter issued ~94 minutes after complaint.</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-12-31"><time datetime="2025-12-31">Dec 31, 2025</time>ADA Sean Mulville responds to bodycam request: "I checked our systems. I do not see it." The statement is passive — he checked whether PPD had uploaded it, not whether it existed or whether he should demand it. Under <em>Kyles v. Whitley</em>, police possession is prosecution possession. The DA has an obligation to obtain and disclose, not just check a database. Four ADAs assigned to this case. None compelled production. The footage moved from "doesn't exist" (building lie) to "can't be found" (system failure) to institutional forgetting.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-04-15"><time datetime="2026-04-15">Apr 15, 2026</time>Same evening as leasing-office video, Justin files harassment report.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-10"><time datetime="2026-05-10">May 10, 2026</time>Upon reporting witness intimidation and retaliation, Cpl. Snyder (Badge #8068) argued for seven minutes before agreeing to write a report. He called the account 'a made up story.' When shown evidence, he stated: 'I'm not interested in a plethora of evidence.' He then characterized the situation as 'crazy' — his own word, not the complainant's. The seven-minute resistance to documenting the report is itself corroboration of the severity he resisted acknowledging. Report eventually filed under DC #26-09-0597175.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-06-12"><time datetime="2026-06-12">Jun 12, 2026</time>Trial date.</li>
                    </ol>
                </article>

                <article class="track gold" id="track-trust" aria-labelledby="track-family">
                    <h3 id="track-family">Track 3 - The Family / Trust</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li data-date="1993"><time datetime="1993">1993</time>Jennifer Horn Family Trust established.</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-02"><time datetime="2025-02">Feb 2025</time>Trustee: "I will be cutting back on all your supplemental monies for everything, since you are giving up the disability. It would be better if you get the disability until you get yourself self-sufficient. Your choices affect me, and I'm telling you that I'm at my limits."</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-02-21"><time datetime="2025-02-21">Feb 21, 2025</time>Justin rejects the coercion: "You want to punish me for wanting to work? For needing a valid ID? Coercing me to go for disability? That's over." The trustee repeats days later: "So if you choose to ditch the disability, you will have to get by with less support from me."</li>
                        <li data-date="2025-03-28"><time datetime="2025-03-28">Mar 28, 2025</time>Trust amendment reduces cap from 10% to 5%.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-02-28"><time datetime="2026-02-28">Feb 28, 2026</time>License expires; father continues paying landlord over written objection.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-01"><time datetime="2026-05-01">May 1, 2026</time>10K relocation request refused ("Why should I jeopardize my credit?").</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-06"><time datetime="2026-05-06">May 6, 2026</time>Ambulance day; trust channel still tied to same property payments.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-07"><time datetime="2026-05-07">May 7, 2026</time>"You do not have my permission to come to my house."</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-14"><time datetime="2026-05-14">May 14, 2026</time>Eight days after the ambulance, the trustee funds furnished relocation housing — via personal credit card. The capacity existed on May 1. He chose May 14. The timing is itself evidence: help arrived only after the crisis became undeniable, not when it was requested.</li>
                        <li data-date="2026-05-10"><time datetime="2026-05-10">May 10, 2026</time>"Check the mail" while holding tracking number.</li>
                    </ol>
                </article>
            </div>

            <div class="quote-grid" aria-label="Primary quote anchors">
                <blockquote class="pullquote">
                    "Then you're welcome to break your lease and move out."
                    <cite>Nicole Cordial, Apr 15, 2026</cite>
                </blockquote>
                <blockquote class="pullquote teal">
                    "I'm not interested in a plethora of evidence."
                    <cite>Cpl. Snyder, May 10, 2026</cite>
                </blockquote>
                <blockquote class="pullquote gold">
                    "You do not have my permission to come to my house."
                    <cite>Dr. Abraham S. Horn, May 7, 2026</cite>
                </blockquote>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

